solution:
This is a finite geometric series with first term $\frac{1}{2}$, common ratio $\frac{1}{2}$ and $10$ terms. Therefore the sum is: $$\frac{\frac{1}{2}\left(1-\frac{1}{2^{10}}\right)}{1-\frac{1}{2}}
=\frac{\frac{2^{10}-1}{2^{11}}}{\frac{1}{2}}
= \frac{2^{10}-1}{2^{10}}=\boxed{\frac{1023}{1024}}.$$

problem:
Let \[f(x) =
\begin{cases}
3x + 5 &\text{if }x<-3, \\
7-4x&\text{if }x\ge -3.
\end{cases}
\]Find $f(-10)$.

solution:
We have  \begin{align*}
\frac{12}{x \cdot x} \cdot \frac{x^4}{14x}\cdot \frac{35}{3x} &=
\frac{12 \cdot x^4 \cdot 35}{x^2\cdot 14x \cdot 3x}\\& = \frac{(4 \cdot 3) \cdot (5 \cdot 7) \cdot x^4}{(3 \cdot 2 \cdot 7)(x^2 \cdot x \cdot x)}\\
&= \frac{2\cdot 2 \cdot 3 \cdot 5 \cdot 7}{2 \cdot 3 \cdot 7}\cdot\frac{x^4}{x^{4}}\\
&= 2 \cdot 5 = \boxed{10}.
\end{align*}

