Solve the following system of equations for $c$:
\begin{align*}
a - b &= 2 (c+d)\\
b &= a-2 \\
d &= c+5
\end{align*}

solution:
Rearranging $x^2 - x - 1= 0$ gives $x^2 = x + 1$.  So, repeatedly substituting $x+1$ for $x^2$ gives us \begin{align*}
x^3 - 2x + 1 &= x(x^2)-2x + 1\\
&=x(x+1) - 2x + 1\\
&= x^2 + x -2x + 1\\
&= x^2 - x + 1\\
&= (x+1) - x + 1\\
&=\boxed{2}
\end{align*}

